### File Upload Demo — API Requests
### Compatible with IntelliJ HTTP Client and VS Code REST Client extension
### Run the app first: ./mvnw spring-boot:run

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### AUTH
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Register a new user
### Expected: 200 OK — { "token": "eyJ...", "username": "alice", "role": "ROLE_USER" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("user_token", response.body.token);
    client.global.set("username", response.body.username);
%}

###

### 2. Register a second user (for access-control tests)
### Expected: 200 OK
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("other_token", response.body.token);
%}

###

### 3. Register — duplicate username
### Expected: 400 Bad Request — { "error": "Username already taken" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "anotherpassword"
}

###

### 4. Register — username too short (< 3 chars)
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "ab",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 5. Register — password too short (< 6 chars)
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "charlie",
  "password": "abc"
}

###

### 6. Login — success
### Expected: 200 OK — { "token": "eyJ...", "username": "alice", "role": "ROLE_USER" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("user_token", response.body.token);
%}

###

### 7. Login — wrong password
### Expected: 401 Unauthorized — { "error": "Invalid credentials" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### 8. Login — unknown user
### Expected: 401 Unauthorized — { "error": "Invalid credentials" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "nobody",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 9. Login — locked account (after 5 failed attempts)
### Expected: 423 Locked — { "error": "Account is locked due to too many failed login attempts" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "lockeduser",
  "password": "anypassword"
}


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### FILES — requires valid JWT in user_token / admin_token variables above
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 10. Upload a text file
### Expected: 200 OK — FileMetadataDto with scanStatus: "CLEAN"
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello from the API request file!
--boundary--

> {%
    client.global.set("file_id", response.body.id);
%}

###

### 11. Upload a blocked extension (.exe)
### Expected: 422 Unprocessable Entity — { "error": "File type not allowed: .exe" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="virus.exe"
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

This pretends to be an executable
--boundary--

###

### 12. Upload a shell script (.sh)
### Expected: 422 Unprocessable Entity — { "error": "File type not allowed: .sh" }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="deploy.sh"
Content-Type: text/plain

#!/bin/bash
echo "blocked"
--boundary--

###

### 13. Upload with path traversal in filename
### Expected: 200 OK — originalFilename sanitized (../ replaced with _)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="../../etc/passwd"
Content-Type: text/plain

fake content
--boundary--

###

### 14. Upload without authentication
### Expected: 401 or 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

content
--boundary--

###

### 15. List own files
### Expected: 200 OK — array of FileMetadataDto belonging to the authenticated user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}

###

### 16. List own files — no auth
### Expected: 401 or 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files

###

### 17. Download file by ID (as owner)
### Expected: 200 OK — file bytes, Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="..."
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{file_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}

###

### 18. Download file by ID (as other user — non-owner)
### Expected: 403 Forbidden — { "error": "Access denied" }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{file_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{other_token}}

###

### 19. Get file metadata
### Expected: 200 OK — { id, originalFilename, mimeType, size, scanStatus, ownerUsername, createdAt }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{file_id}}/meta
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}

###

### 20. Get metadata as non-owner
### Expected: 403 Forbidden — { "error": "Access denied" }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{file_id}}/meta
Authorization: Bearer {{other_token}}

###

### 21. Delete file (as owner)
### Expected: 204 No Content
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{file_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}

###

### 22. Delete file (as non-owner)
### Expected: 403 Forbidden — { "error": "Access denied" }
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{file_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{other_token}}

###

### 23. List ALL files — admin only
### First register an admin manually or set ROLE_ADMIN in DB,
### then log in and capture the token as admin_token.
### Expected: 200 OK — all files from all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/all
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}

###

### 24. List all files as a regular user
### Expected: 403 Forbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/all
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}

###

### 25. Download non-existent file ID
### Expected: 500 Internal Server Error — { "error": "File not found: 999999" }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/999999
Authorization: Bearer {{user_token}}
